recordings.rmk: Recorded in a hotel garden; parrotbills were certainly present but I am not totally certain the bird recorded was one; the only other small passerine present as a possibility was White-rumped Munia, but the parrotbill seems to best match other XC recordings. Recorded with Zoom H2n digital recorder in .wav format; normalized; later converted to mp3.
A noisy combination of typical call and the “wee-wee-wee” song. Edited: High pass 245Hz, 20db/decade; Amplify 30db. Olympus LS-14.
